     solution 'x', where 'f' is an n vector and L is the n \times n
     matrix
     [ b[0] c[0]           a[0]   ]
     [ a[1] b[1] c[1]             ]
     [      a[2] b[2] c[2]        ]
     [                ...         ]
     [ c[n-1]       a[n-1] b[n-1] ]
     For Dirichlet boundary conditions (denoted here by 'u[-1]' and
     'u[n]'), replace 'f[0]' by 'f[0]-a[0]u[-1]' and
     'f[n-1]-c[n-1]u[n]'; then set 'a[0]=c[n-1]=0'.

